reviews.review_text: Love it '92 is pretty damn cool if you go looking . . . some diamonds in the rough, such as this. Great stuff all the way through. Shakedown (with some hilarious punches, like a horn section), Foolish Heart, Eyes, So Many Roads, Dew, Johnny B.

Trash can gold 3 great shows.  What a great Memorial Day weekend.  Where did these kind go to? I do remember Vince and his keyboard turning into a giant Mayan temple with head and arms at this show, while playing.  It was quite a sight to behold while I danced and laughed my arse off on that steep Shoreline grass!!   I am not too fond of really any Shakedowns with Vince, but this one live and played later is well worth the listen.  Excellent, vibrant Foolish Heart. Jerry is pretty on tonight.

Pay me back someday..... As much as I hated the "pre-recorded" digi drums from Mickey, they're used sparingly here - and the last couple of minutes of "Corina" (*shudder*) into the drumz sequence ain't half bad.  Surprisingly strong, actually.  Nothing to write home about, but a set of headphones and the proper frame of mind will give you an enjoyable experience.
Excellent, overlooked Dew The gem of this show is the Morning Dew. If the band walks offstage after a Dew, typically its an above average performance and this one doesn't disappoint.

GD Radio on Sirius I was listening to This Day in History on Sirius radio when they played a couple tunes from the concert so I had to come here to listen to the entire show.  WOW   Very impressed and what a great morning dew!

Thanks for this I really enjoyed streaming this one today at work...while pounding out some Java code.

I don't normally jump to '92 or beyond when I look for "this day in history" shows but glad I went for it today.  Some great playing here, love the Eyes jam in particular and yes the Morning Dew is moving...Jerry belting it out!  

Sorry, but I'm a fan of Corrina :-) so I like all versions I've heard haha.  The drums/space was pretty trippy too.

Thanks to all who had a part in bringing this lovely music to my ears today.
Great show from 92 Glad I stumbled upon this one on this day in history!
